On June 6, 1944, thousands of Allied Soldiers landed on the beaches of Normandy. The odds were stacked against them but, they prevailed. The mission turned the tide of the war in the favor of the Allies, laying the foundation for victory. Today, we say thank you to all who were there that day. Your bravery, courage, and sacrifice will never be forgotten, and the free world is forever grateful for your actions on that day 75 years ago.

Today is a day to remember all that is required to maintain freedom. It does not come without sacrifice. Thank you to the men and women who have served and sacrificed for this nation. We will always remember!
